-- CarbonDesk of London to Open Geneva Office With Staff of Three on Oct. 1
-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 2010-09-21T09:21:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/carbondesk-of-london-to-open-geneva-office-with-staff-of-three-on-oct-1.html
CarbonDesk Ltd., a London-based
broker of emission permits, plans to open an office in Geneva on
Oct. 1  CarbonDesk has hired two brokers and will move Jay Ward,
its London-based options broker, to the Geneva office, company
Chief Executive Officer Brett Stacey said today in an inteview.
He declined to name the two brokers.  “A lot of big power companies have got trading desks over
there, and hedge funds are moving out to Geneva and Zurich,”
Stacey said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
